value.title: Presidential Transition Live Updates: House Says It Will Move Swiftly With Impeachment If Pence Won’t Act
value.excerpt: The House could vote as soon as Tuesday on charging President Trump with inciting a mob that attacked the Capitol. But top leaders want to avoid hamstringing the first days of Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s presidency with an all-consuming Senate trial.

value.title: Pence will attend Biden's inauguration
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence will attend the inauguration of President-elect Joe Biden, according to a source familiar.

value.title: Mediaite: Parler CEO says it took down post from Lin Wood calling for Mike Pence's execution
value.excerpt: The CEO of Parler, a social media platform popular among conservatives, told Mediaite that it removed a post from attorney Lin Wood calling for Vice President Mike Pence to be executed by "firing squads."

value.title: Pence has not ruled out 25th Amendment, source says
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence has not ruled out an effort to invoke the 25th Amendment and wants to preserve the option in case President Donald Trump becomes more unstable, a source close to the vice president says.

value.title: Republican Sen. Pat Toomey says he thinks Trump 'committed impeachable offenses'
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Pat Toomey of Pennsylvania said Saturday he thinks President Donald Trump "committed impeachable offenses," but said he is not certain attempting to remove the President from office with just a few days left in his term is the right course of action.

value.title: Trump considering Giuliani and Dershowitz for impeachment defense team
value.excerpt: Staring down the barrel of a second impeachment, President Donald Trump is beginning to mull who would represent him in a Senate trial.

value.title: Meena Harris, Building That Brand
value.excerpt: Kamala Harris’s niece is building her own empire with statement T-shirts. Just don’t define her by her family.

value.title: Trump administration strikes parting blow at Medicaid with Tennessee block grant
value.excerpt: Just days before leaving office, the Trump administration took a step toward fulfilling a long-held Republican dream of curbing Medicaid costs and giving states more flexibility to run the program.

value.title: Read: House Democrats' draft of a new article of impeachment against Trump
value.excerpt: House Democrats have circulated a draft of a new impeachment resolution against President Donald Trump with one article of impeachment, "incitement of insurrection."

value.title: Nikki Haley says Trump's post-election actions will be 'judged harshly by history'
value.excerpt: Former UN ambassador Nikki Haley distanced herself from her onetime boss, President Donald Trump, in a closed-door speech on Thursday night, telling members of the Republican National Committee that the President's actions after the election "will be judged harshly by history."

value.title: Josh Hawley's ploy to be a pro-Trump hero results in withering blowback
value.excerpt: Missouri Sen. Josh Hawley offered pro-Trump demonstrators who stood outside the Capitol a raised fist salute as he walked into the Senate early on Wednesday, buoyant about his leading role in objecting to President Donald Trump's electoral defeat.

value.title: Pelosi asks Joint Chiefs about preventing Trump from launching nukes
value.excerpt: House Speaker Nancy Pelosi spoke with the nation's top military officer on Friday about precautions in place to prevent President Donald Trump from ordering a nuclear strike or conducting other military hostilities as Democrats seek his removal from office.

value.title: POLITICO-Harvard poll: Public strongly backs Biden's demand for Covid aid
value.excerpt: There's strong public support for Biden's vision of an expansive government effort to combat the pandemic and its economic fallout.

value.title: With Merrick Garland pick, Biden signals stark contrast with Trump on Justice Department
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump declared nearly a year ago, "I am actually, I guess, the chief law enforcement officer," as he tried to assert control over Department of Justice decisions.

value.title: Hear why Klobuchar fist-bumped Pence after Electoral certification
value.excerpt: Sen. Amy Klobuchar (D-MN), tells CNN's Chris Cuomo about the moment Congress finalized President-elect Joe Biden's victory, and about why she chose to fist-bump Vice President Mike Pence after he read the election results.

value.title: Trump's Education Secretary Betsy DeVos submits resignation
value.excerpt: Education Secretary Betsy DeVos has submitted her resignation, making her the second Cabinet member to resign over President Donald Trump's response to the mob breaching the US Capitol on Wednesday, according to an official.

value.title: Prosecutors 'looking at all actors,' including Trump, as charges are filed against Capitol rioters
value.excerpt: Federal investigators are looking at everyone involved in the unrest at the US Capitol on Wednesday, including the role President Donald Trump played in inciting the crowd, the acting US attorney in Washington, DC, said Thursday.

value.title: 'His entire legacy was wiped out yesterday': Hill Republicans ready to move on from Trump
value.excerpt: Congressional Republicans are done with Donald Trump.

value.title: Joe Biden: Black Lives Matter protesters would have been ‘treated differently’ at Capitol demonstrations
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden called protesters at the Capitol a “mob of thugs” and said if they were a group of Black Lives Matter demonstrators they would have been “treated very differently.”

value.title: Graham: Trump and I have had a hell of a journey, but enough is enough
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Lindsey Graham, who has been a staunch supporter of President Trump, vigorously defended to certify the electoral college votes on the Senate floor.

value.title: Analysis: No, Mike Pence can't steal the election for Trump
value.excerpt: This is it. President Donald Trump's dogged effort to ignore the voters, state election officials, the courts and the Electoral College has come down to his latest wild idea -- that he'll just get Vice President Mike Pence to steal the thing for him.

value.title: 'It's a dark place': Trump's call a window into a President consumed
value.excerpt: President Donald Trump had been trying for weeks to get Georgia's secretary of state on the phone.

value.title: Georgia's Raffensperger says he 'never believed' it appropriate to speak with Trump about election
value.excerpt: The Republican secretary of state also said the call from Trump could warrant an investigation into possible conflicts of interest.

value.title: Harris lambasts Trump call with Georgia officials as 'bold abuse of power'
value.excerpt: Vice President-elect Kamala Harris slammed President Donald Trump and his call pushing Georgia Secretary of State Brad Raffensperger to "find" votes to overturn the election results, a "bald-faced, bold abuse of power," in Savannah, Georgia, on Sunday.

value.title: Trump to award Medal of Freedom to GOP Reps. Devin Nunes and Jim Jordan
value.excerpt: Before he leaves office, President Donald Trump will award the nation's highest civilian honor to two of his most vocal political allies who defended him throughout his impeachment, Rep. Devin Nunes of California and Rep. Jim Jordan of Ohio, as the White House has been inundated with requests for others,

value.title: Pence 'welcomes' congressional Republicans' bid to challenge electoral votes
value.excerpt: Vice President Mike Pence on Saturday signaled his support for a bid by Republicans lawmakers to challenge electoral votes when Congress is expected to certify President-elect Joe Biden's victory in a meeting this week.

value.title: US surgeon general: 'No reason to doubt' Covid-19 death toll number after Trump claims deaths 'exaggerated'
value.excerpt: US Surgeon General Dr. Jerome Adams on Sunday said he has "no reason to doubt" the US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention's Covid-19 death toll, contradicting President Donald Trump's claim that the agency has "exaggerated" its numbers.

value.title: Federal judge throws out Gohmert lawsuit asking Pence to interfere in Electoral College count
value.excerpt: A federal judge threw out a lawsuit from Rep. Louie Gohmert of Texas and several Arizona Republicans seeking to force Vice President Mike Pence to help throw the election to President Donald Trump next week when Congress meets to count the Electoral College votes.

value.title: What Will Pence Do When Congress Counts the Votes?
value.excerpt: Readers are shocked that the question is being asked and speculate that the vice president may find an excuse not to be present. They also criticize Senator Josh Hawley.

value.title: With Trump a no-show, Mar-a-Lago guests left to party maskless with Rudy Giuliani and Vanilla Ice
value.excerpt: Guests who paid four-figures for tickets to President Donald Trump's annual New Year's Eve party were left to party with his personal attorney Rudy Giuliani, his two adult sons and various figures from the conservative media — none of whom wore masks — after the President made a last-minute decision
